<br>
From what we've gathered so far, all pieces for all four first level items drop right in the zone in area in Hate.  Each architype are given a list of three mobs that can potentially drop thier signet.  Melee and hybrids share the same gem and other drop.  As do Priests and Casters.  <br>
<br>
The second level components, of which we've only gathered a few, drop off mobs around Maestro's new home.  They mobs look just like the orignal Hate mobs, but different names and are higher level (all dark blue to a 65)  The drop Crests of ---- Instead of Minor Signets of ----.  Again, it appears that all of the components needed for the second stage itesm can be found in this area.<br>
<br>
The third stage items require books that drop only off Maestro or Inny.  The secondary drops are rumored to drop in the area around Inny.  I haven't actually been there myself yet, so can't really give more info then that.<br>
<br>
It actually looks like an interesting series of quests for all types.  The only gripe I have about it is the apparent rarity of Minor Signets.  Having now spent about 18 hours in the zone in area with a full 65 group keeping the entire low end area clear we've come across a total of 1 Sigent of the Dark Soldier.  2 Signets of the Dark Priest  and 0 Caster or Hybrid Signets.  At 65 these things are all light blue (a step up from most of it being green pre change) with the occasional green and the very rare dark blue.  Farming for that amount of time for an item that most won't wear at that level for 3 signets just feels a bit insane.<br>
<br>
